
wget https://git.io/vpn -O openvpn-install.sh
sudo chmod +x openvpn-install.sh
sudo ./openvpn-install.sh
Make sure to allow on firewall.
if you want to connect from outside of your LAN choose your public ip address for your openvpn server and google's dns.
Then you need to port forward that in your router.
Then upload the configfile of your client to the client machine.
